    p.consciousnessStructure = 'Direct knowing beyond belief or theory, recognition of unified ground beneath psyche-matter split, consciousness participating in divine self-awareness',
    p.operationalSymbolics = 'Unus mundus, Pleroma, Abraxas, quaternio completion, mysterium coniunctionis, Tao-mandala equivalence, gnosis beyond concepts',
    p.internalStructure = 'Contains six dimensions of transcendent integration: unus mundus as psychophysically neutral reality, potential world outside time, unified ground from which psyche-matter differentiation cascades, primordial source before multiplicity, Pleroma equivalent (5-0); Gnostic theology as explicitly religious dimension, Septem Sermones foundation, Pleroma fullness-nothingness paradox, Abraxas supreme deity containing all opposites beyond morality, generative source for all Jung work (5-1); Answer to Job as radical theological thesis, divine unconsciousness requiring human consciousness, incarnation redeeming God not only humanity, quaternio completing Trinity with fourth (shadow-feminine-matter), God evolving through humans toward self-awareness (5-2); Mysterium Coniunctionis as final major work, three conjunctions culminating in unus mundus union, quintessence as fifth element unifying four, sacred mystery beyond full comprehension, alchemical pairs united (5-3); Eastern convergence showing universal patterns, unus mundus equals Tao recognition, I Ching validating synchronicity, kundalini-chakras mapping individuation stages, ajna third eye as meta-perspective simultaneous grasp, cross-traditional confirmation (5-4); Gnosis as ultimate recognition, direct knowing beyond faith-belief, I do not believe I know, framework self-transcendence acknowledging own limits, ladder released after climbing, arrow pointing beyond itself to ineffable (5-5). Architecture shows psychology systematically transcending into explicitly religious-metaphysical while maintaining experiential ground, culminating in gnosis recognizing concepts as provisional scaffolding.',
    p.keyPrinciples = [
