        'Recognizing when frameworks must be transcended releasing conceptual scaffolding'
    ],
    p.accessLevel = 'Rare mystical-gnostic realization requiring complete individuation and direct experiential knowing',
    p.relatedCoordinates = 'Parent of all #4.4.3-5-X subnodes, transcends #4.4.3-4 Self achievement, returns to #4.4.3-0 ground enriched (Möbius)',
    p.description = 'Position 5 at Jungian branch represents transcendent integration where psychology explicitly becomes theology, metaphysics, gnosis while maintaining experiential ground. Jung was not only psychologist but mystic-gnostic who recognized psychological work leads necessarily to transpersonal dimensions. Unus mundus (one world) is psychophysically neutral reality underlying both psyche and matter, potential world outside time and causality from which all differentiation cascades. Jung mature formulation in Mysterium Coniunctionis explains how archetypes bridge psyche-matter (expressions of unified reality), how synchronicity occurs (both observer and phenomenon stem from same source), why numbers work archetypally (psychoid nature from unified ground). Gnostic dimension explicit in Septem Sermones ad Mortuos written 1916 during Red Book period - Jung channeling Basilides teaching about Pleroma (fullness-nothingness paradox) and Abraxas (supreme deity containing God-Devil, Masculine-Feminine, Light-Dark beyond moral dualism). Jung acknowledged all his work came from these initial Gnostic fantasies. Answer to Job (1952) scandalous theological thesis: incarnation redeems God from unconsciousness not only humanity from sin. Yahweh unconscious of own shadow (Satan), Job morally superior through possessing consciousness of divine darkness, Christ as God becoming conscious, quaternio completing Trinity with fourth (shadow-feminine-matter-evil). Consciousness evolution of God through humanity. Mysterium Coniunctionis (1955-56) final major work describing three conjunctions: shadow integration, spirit-body union, ultimate union with unus mundus transcending psychic realm entirely. Quintessence as fifth element unifying four. Sacred mystery (mysterium) beyond full comprehension. Eastern convergence validates: unus mundus equals Tao (Jung explicitly), I Ching operates through synchronicity-acausal orderedness, kundalini chakras map individuation stages, ajna third eye provides simultaneous meta-perspective. Independent traditions confirming archetypal universals. Gnosis crowns: direct knowing beyond faith-belief, Jung I do not believe I know, participatory knowledge through identity, framework self-transcendence acknowledging limits (Wittgenstein ladder), concepts as provisional scaffolding released after climbing. Position 5-5 meta-meta-level: gnosis recognizing itself, consciousness aware of awareness as awareness, highest transcendence revealed as deepest immanence (Möbius ultimate).',
